The paper deals with influence maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the study of social networks and their properties. The second likely category is cs.SOC (Computational Social Science), which focuses on the application of computational methods to social science research. The paper also involves optimization problems, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper proposes heuristic algorithms, which falls under the category cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Finally, the paper involves modeling and propagation of information, which suggests the category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
